Update! Winner was announced on live and contacted through email! 
♥️My loves!♥️ Let’s celebrate the NEW YEAR with a raffle to win a $500 tattoo!
RULES:

-I will ONLY be accepting raffles bought *THROUGH MY WEBSITE*! Link is in my bio!
(Don’t let any scammers try and trick you into Venmo or anything!!)

-Each ticket is $10 and you can buy as many as you want! Every ticket = 1 entry! 

-The winner will be chosen at ✨5pm MST January 1!✨

-Last rule! You have to dig the tattoos that I do! Please don’t enter and then ask for a photo realism portrait of your grandma…please. Why? Because I would do a terrible job at that! 🥰 Meaning: only enter if you love what I do! ♥️

Tell your friends!!

I LOVE YOU!!!!!!!!

I can’t lie…I’m feeling quite scared of 2023, but I’m doing my best to remain hopeful and optimistic about the coming year.🥹
 
I’m so grateful for the amazing people in my life, though! I swear, my wonderful (and very patient) husband needs a fucking trophy. 😅♥️ I couldn’t do this without his love and support. 

But the biggest THANK YOU goes to y’all! 

Thank you for supporting my art, my business @loveyoutattoo_boulder, and for wanting to get tattooed by me! 

LOVE Y’ALL ♥️ cj

The world said goodbye to one of the silliest of gooses today - my sweet, hilarious, loving, and all around amazing Grandpa - or Poppie, as we like to call him. 

He loved to dance, he loved his pets, he LOVED (and I mean LOOOOOVED) being the center of attention and making people laugh, but most of all he loved his family. 
And holy hell am I grateful to be in that category. 

I have too many funny stories to even tell, but I can say this - to know Poppie, was to love Poppie. 

We love you so much, Pop. ♥️

Happy Mother’s Day to my bestie ♥️ I am always (and I mean ALWAYS) grateful that you are my momma. I wouldn’t be who I am without you, Bo, and Nannie to guide me and show me what being a strong, loving, and empathetic woman looks like. 
I LOVE YOU. See you soon. Wish it was for happier reasons, but I’ll take what I can get. @jerrijamesart

Yesterday we said goodbye to our Beni / Cheese Boy / Bubba / Jason’s Dog / Not My Dog / Big Dummy / Ol’ Crazy Eyes. 💔
If you knew Beni, you knew he wasn’t exactly the easiest dog to have and my god could he just be so damn annoying, but we loved him all the same and saying goodbye has broken our hearts. Especially Jason. (If you know my husband send him some love please) They had such a deep connection and Beni was his shadow from day one. 

Going from 3 pets to 1 pet in just a little over a year has been so damn hard, but we’re thankful for the memories and the love our critters have shown us and we wouldn’t take any of it back.

Hi bb’s. In case we haven’t met, I’m Cori. 
I am the proud owner of the cutest tattoo shop in the entire world (in my personal, very biased opinion) @loveyoutattoo_boulder. 
I’ve been tattooing for 11 years and specialize in doing traditional tattoos with a twist…or a butt. 
I love tattooing, but I truly adore getting to know my clients- laughing, trauma bonding, talking about tv shows or the smutty fantasy books I’m obsessed with (@therealsjmaas I’m lookin at you), etc etc. 
I try my best to be a positive and cheerful person (though I am medicated for having too much sad in my system) and I always want my clients to feel welcomed and comfortable to be themselves! 
Okay, I’m done. Love you! Byyyyyyyeeeee!
